' Umar al - Tilmisani ( Arabic : عمر التلمسانى‎ , IPA : ( ˈʕomɑɾˤ et.telmeˈsæːni ) ; most often transliterated as Omar el Telmesany or Telmesani ) ( 4 November 1904 - 22 May 1986 ) was the third General Guide ( Murshid al-'Am ) of the Egyptian Muslim Brothers .
Pedro León Zapata ( 27 February 1929 -- 6 February 2015 ) was a prominent Venezuelan artist , humorist and cartoonist .
V. C. Palanisami Gounder ( died 15 April 1965 ) was an Indian merchant and politician of the Indian National Congress who served as Minister of Prohibition of the Madras State in the cabinet of C. Rajagopalachari and Minister for Animal Husbandry and Harijan Welfare in K. Kamaraj 's cabinet .
Karl August Ferdinand von Borcke ( 18 February 1776 -- 15 December 1830 ) was a Prussian general and the first recipient of the Iron Cross .
William Piercy , 1st Baron Piercy CBE ( 7 February 1886 -- 7 July 1966 ) , was a British economist , civil servant , businessman and financier .
Mezezius ( /mɨˈziːʒəs/ ; Greek : Μιζίζιος ; Armenian : Մժէժ , Mžēž or Mzhezh ) was an Armenian noble who served as a general of Byzantium , later usurping the Byzantine throne in Sicily from 668 to 669 .
Richard Kilvington ( c. 1302 - 1361 ) was an English scholastic philosopher at the University of Oxford .
Caleb Banks ( 18 September 1659 - 13 September 1696 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons between 1685 and 1696 .
Benjamin Gumbs II ( died 1768 ) was a British colonial governor and sugarcane plantation owner on Katouche Bay .
Emerson Hough ( 1857 - -1923 ) was an American author best known for writing western stories and historical novels .
Wu Kung - i or Wu Gongyi ( 1898 - -1970 ) was a well - known teacher of the soft style martial art t'ai chi ch'uan ( taijiquan ) in China , and , after 1949 , in the British colony of Hong Kong .
Alison Brading ( 26 February 1939 - 7 January 2011 ) was a British scientist who studied the physiology and pharmacology of smooth muscle , particularly in the urinary tract .
Mordecai Ehrenpreis ( later on : Marcus Ehrenpreis ; 25 June 1869 -- 26 February 1951 ) was a Hebrew author , publisher , Rabbi and Zionist .
Charles Ryle Fay ( 13 January 1884 -- 19 November 1961 ) was a British economic historian .
Henriette Jørgensen ( 1791 - -1847 ) was a Danish stage actress and translator .
Royal Dixon ( 25 March 1885 - - 4 June 1962 ) was an American author , animal rights activist and a member of the Americanization movement .
Suzanne Dalbert ( 12 May 1927 -- 31 December 1970 ) was a French actress who appeared in a number of American films and television series during the 1940s and 1950s .
Sir Glanmor Williams ( 5 May 1920 -- 24 February 2005 ) was one of Wales 's most eminent historians .
Bishop Patrick Collier DD ( 13 January 1880 -- 10 January 1964 ) was an Irish Roman Catholic priest , later appointed as Bishop of Ossory .
Severin Cornet ( c. 1530 -- March 1582 ) was a Franco - Flemish singer , conductor and composer .
Anne Carr , Countess of Bedford ( 9 December 1615 -- 10 May 1684 ) was a wealthy English noblewoman , and the wife of William Russell , 5th Earl of Bedford , a peer and soldier during the English Civil War , who after her death was created Duke of Bedford .
Nico Dostal ( full name : Nikolaus Josef Michael Dostal ) ( 27 November 1895 - -27 October 1981 ) was an Austrian operetta and film music composer .
Chris Braithwaite , also known as Chris Jones ( 1885 - 9 September 1944 ) , was a black Barbadian who was leader of the Colonial Seamen 's Association in the 1930s .
Sears Gallagher ( 1869 - 1955 ) was a prolific , commercially successful American artist proficient in multiple media : drawing , etching , watercolor and oil painting .
John Thompson , 1st Baron Haversham ( c. 1648 -- 1 November 1710 ) , known as Sir John Thompson , Bt , between 1673 and 1696 , was an English politician .
Colonel Atilla Altıkat was the Turkish military attaché to Ottawa , Canada , who was assassinated in 1982 .
Riho Lahi ( 27 October 1904 -- 23 April 1995 ) was an Estonian writer and journalist , probably best known by his fictional character Kihva Värdi .
Archimandrite Kyprianos ( 1735 -- 1803 est . ) is one of the major Greek Cypriot intellectuals and clerics of the 18th century .
Frederick Augustus , Count of Erbach - Fürstenau ( 5 May 1754 -- 12 March 1784 ) , was a member of the German House of Erbach who held the fiefs of Fürstenau , Michelstadt and Breuberg .
Johann Phillip Fabricius ( 22 January 1711 -- 23 January 1791 ) was a German Christian missionary and a Tamil scholar in later part of his life .
Burl Plunkett ( 1933 - -2008 ) is a former basketball coach .
Marth Euphrasia Eluvathingal also called Saint Euphrasia Eluvathingal baptized as Rosa Eluvathingal ( Malayalam : മാർത്ത് എവുപ്രാസ്യാമ്മ ) ( 17 October 1877 -- 29 August 1952 ) was an Indian Carmelite nun of the Syro - Malabar Church which is an Eastern Catholic Church and a part of the Saint Thomas Christian community in Kerala .
Leon Lichtenstein ( 16 May 1878 -- 21 August 1933 ) was a Polish - German mathematician , who made contributions to the areas of differential equations , conformal mapping , and potential theory .
Thomas Brudenell - Bruce , 1st Earl of Ailesbury KT ( 30 April 1729 - 19 April 1814 ) , styled The Honourable Thomas Brudenell until 1747 and known as The Lord Bruce of Tottenham between 1747 and 1776 , was a British courtier .
Mathias J. Hoven ( July 9 , 1850 -- October 1 , 1901 ) , was twice mayor of Madison , Wisconsin , from 1897 to 1898 and from 1899 to 1901 .
Assen Bossev ( Bulgarian : Асен Босев ) ( 22 November 1913 -- 24 April 1997 ) was a prominent Bulgarian author of children 's literature , as well as a translator from Russian .
Komal Swaminathan ( born on 27 January 1935 at Karaikudi , died 1995 ) was a congressional activist in his early years , a Tamil theater personality , film director , and a journalist .
Derek Bryce - Smith ( 1926 - -2011 ) was a chemist at the University of Reading .
Count József Somssich de Saárd ( 9 December 1864 -- 22 January 1941 ) was a Hungarian politician , who served as Minister of Foreign Affairs between 1919 and 1920 .
Hans Hollein ( 30 March 1934 -- 24 April 2014 ) was an Austrian architect and designer and key figure of postmodern architecture .
Elisedd ap Gwylog ( died c. 755 ) , also known as Elise , was king of Powys in eastern Wales .
One of Krys ' son , Sebastian , is a four - time American Grammy winner and eight - time Latin Grammy Awards producer and mixer ( as of 2011 ) Leonardo Krys died of a heart attack in Miami , on March 14 , 2009 .
Colin Eggleston ( 23 September 1941 -- 10 August 2002 ) was an Australian writer and director of TV and films .
Thomas Couture ( 21 December 1815 -- 30 March 1879 ) was an influential French history painter and teacher .
Melancthon Williams Jacobus , Sr . ( 19 September 1816 -- 28 October 1876 ) was an American Presbyterian minister and writer .
Lucien Martin ( 30 May 1908 -- 29 October 1950 ) was a Canadian violinist , conductor , and composer .
George Salmon ( 25 September 1819 -- 22 January 1904 ) was an Irish mathematician and Anglican theologian .
Ludovico Vicentino degli Arrighi ( 1475 - -1527 ) was a papal scribe and type designer in Renaissance Italy .
Charles Griffith Wynne ( 14 August 1815 -- 3 March 1874 ) , later known as Charles Wynne - Finch , was a Liberal Tory politician and a Member of Parliament for Caernarfon .
Adriaen van Diest ( 1655 - -1704 ) was a Dutch painter , who worked in England .
Harry Hake Sr . ( 1871 -- 1955 ) was a prominent American architect in Cincinnati , Ohio at the turn of the 20th century .
Laurence Braddon ( died 29 November 1724 ) , was an English politician and writer .
Vladimir Pravdich - Neminsky ( Russian : Владимир Владимирович Правдич-Неминский,Ukrainian : Володимир Володимирович Правдич-Немінський ; 2 July 1879 -- 17 May 1952 ) was Ukrainian and then Soviet physiologist who published the first EEG and the evoked potential of the mammalian brain .
Sir Robert Hutchison , 1st Baronet , FRCP ( 28 October 1871 - 12 February 1960 ) was a Scottish physician and paediatrician , who is well known as the original editor of the medical books , `` Clinical Methods '' and `` Food and the Principles of Dietetics '' .
After Fidler died in 1980 , her publishers and members of the Edinburgh Children 's Book Group established the Kathleen Fidler Award in memory of her work and support for children 's literature .
Astrid Holm ( 29 March 1893 -- 29 October 1961 ) was a Danish theater and film actress whose career began on the stage and in the early silent film era .
Francis James Newman Rogers , KC ( 1791 - -1851 ) , was an English barrister , judge and legal author , Deputy Judge Advocate General from 1842 until his death in 1851 .
Alfonsina Strada ( 16 March 1891 -- 13 September 1959 ) was an Italian cyclist , the only woman to have ridden one of cycling 's three major stage races .
Ivan Fyodorovich Michurin ( 1700 - -1763 ) was a Russian architect whose designs marked a transition of Russian architecture from early Muscovite Baroque to mature Rastrelliesque style .
William Brooke Smith ( died 1908 ) was an American painter and friend of Ezra Pound .
Henry Crowder ( 1890 - -1955 ) was an African - American jazz musician .
Frank Shipley Collins ( 1848 - 1920 ) was an American botanist and algologist specializing in the study of marine algae .
William Talbot Aveline ( 1822 - -1903 ) was a British geologist and archaeologist .
Rollin Lynde Hartt ( 1869 - -1946 ) was an early 20th - century journalist and congregational minister .
Cristofi Cerchez ( 4 July 1872 -- 1955 ) was a Romanian engineer and architect .
Hercules Collins ( died 1702 ) , was an English Baptist minister , author of a revision of the Heidelberg Catechism called the Orthodox Catechism .
Theudebert I ( French : Thibert or Théodebert ) ( c. 500 -- 547 or 548 ) was the Merovingian king of Austrasia from 533 to his death in 548 .
Henry Charles Fehr FRBS ( 4 November 1867 -- 13 May 1940 ) was a British monumental and architectural sculptor active in the late nineteenth and early twentieth centuries .
Enoch Jenkins ( 6 November 1892 -- 4 January 1984 ) was a British sports shooter .
Lasses Birgitta ( died 1550 ) was an alleged Swedish witch .
Kusumkumari Das ( 1875 - -1948 ) was a Bengali poet , writer and social activist .
Ralph Sneyd ( died 1650 ) was an English landowner and politician who sat in the House of Commons from 1640 to 1642 .
Sol Polk ( 1916 - 1988 ) , was an American businessman and co - founder of appliance retailer Polk Brothers .
Marie d'Albret , Countess of Rethel , Countess of Nevers ( 25 March 1491 -- 27 October 1549 ) was the suo jure Countess of Rethel , a title which she inherited at the age of nine upon the death of her mother , Charlotte of Nevers , Sovereign Countess of Rethel , on 23 August 1500 .
Sextus ( possibly Gaius ) Julius Saturninus ( died 280 ) was a Roman usurper against Emperor Probus .
Joan Brickhill ( 6 March 1924 -- 15 January 2014 ) was a South African actress who worked in radio , theatre , film , and television .
Muhammadu Attahiru I ( died 1903 ) was the twelfth Sultan of the Sokoto Caliphate from October 1902 until March 15 , 1903 .
Vendela Skytte ( or Wendela Skytte ) ( 8 December 1608 -- 18 August 1629 ) was a Swedish noblewoman , salonist and writer , poet and Lady of Letters .
Abu Ali Fadhl ibn Hasan Tabarsi ( Persian / Arabic:ابو على فضل بن حسن طبرسى ) known as Shaykh Tabarsi , was a 12th - century Persian Shia scholar who died in 548 AH ( 1153 CE ) .
Maharaj Ghulam Hussain Kathak ( 1905 -- 2001 ) was a classical dancer and teacher for the art . He held the distinction of singularly sustaining the tradition of classical dance in Pakistan and producing students like Nahid Siddiqui , Fasih Ur Rehman , Nighat Chaudry , Amy Minwala and Panna among many others .
Brilliana , Lady Harley ( 1598 -- 29 October 1643 ) , née Brilliana Conway , was a celebrated English letter - writer .
Voldemārs Sudmalis ( 1922 - 1990 ) was a Latvian football defender , one of the most popular post - war footballers from Liepāja .
Kadri Pasha or Mehmet Kadri Pasha ( 1832 - -1884 ) was an Ottoman statesman .
Willem van Ravesteyn ( Rotterdam , 15 October 1876 -- Rotterdam , 10 June 1970 ) was a Dutch Communist politician and historian .
Frederick William III , Duke of Schleswig - Holstein - Sonderburg - Beck ( 4 November 1723 -- 6 May 1757 ) was a son of Frederick William II and his wife , Ursula Anna of Dohna .
Notker Physicus ( died 12 November 975 ) , sometimes called Notker II , was a physician , painter , and composer .
Egil Hjorth - Jenssen ( 18 April 1893 -- 8 November 1969 ) was a Norwegian actor and theatre director .
Louise - Anastasia Serment ( Grenoble , 1642 - Paris , 1692 ) was a French natural philosopher and poet .
George J. Gaskin ( 1863 - -1920 ) was an Irish Tenor based in the United States .
Hamilton Hume ( 19 June 1797 -- 19 April 1873 ) was an early explorer of the present - day Australian states of New South Wales and Victoria .
Girolamo Belli ( 1552 -- c. 1620 ) was an Italian composer and music teacher of the late Renaissance .
Henry Paget , 2nd Marquess of Anglesey Bt , PC , DL ( 6 July 1797 -- 7 February 1869 ) , styled Lord Paget 1812 and 1815 and Earl of Uxbridge from 1815 to 1854 , was a British peer and Whig politician .
William Capell , 3rd Earl of Essex , KG PC ( 11 January 1697 -- 8 January 1743 ) was an English courtier and diplomat .
Jerry Dreva ( 1945 - -1997 ) was an artist , writer , performer , activist and teacher from South Milwaukee , Wisconsin .
Francis Coudrill ( born 1913 in Warwick - died 1989 ) was an English artist and ventriloquist , most notable for being the creator of Hank the Cowboy .
Věra Chytilová ( 2 February 1929 -- 12 March 2014 ) was an avant - garde Czech film director and pioneer of Czech cinema .
Gilbert West ( 1703 - -1756 ) was a minor English poet , translator and Christian apologist in the early and middle eighteenth century .
William Frederick Lake Price ( 1810 - -1896 ) was an English watercolourist and an innovator in mid - nineteenth century photography .
Sir Henry Pollexfen ( 1632 -- 15 June 1691 ) was a British judge and politician .
Louisa Hawkins Canby ( December 25 , 1818 -- 1889 ) was nicknamed the `` Angel of Santa Fe '' in 1862 for her compassion toward sick , wounded , and freezing Confederate soldiers at Santa Fe , New Mexico .
Wayne Jarratt ( 19 April 1957 -- 14 May 1988 ) was an Australian stage and television actor in the 1980s , remembered for his role of friendly prison officer Steve Faulkner in the soap opera Prisoner .
Edward Carlyon Eliot ( 1879 - -1940 ) was a British diplomat and Colonial Service administrator .
Adolf Portmann ( 27 May 1897 -- 28 June 1982 ) was a zoologist .
Countess Margit Teleki de Szék ( 2 December 1860 -- 26 January 1922 ) was a Hungarian noblewoman , wife of Prime Minister Károly Khuen - Héderváry .
Thomas Howard , 8th Duke of Norfolk , Earl Marshal ( 11 December 1683 -- 23 December 1732 ) was the son of Lord Thomas Howard ( of Worksop ) and Mary Elizabeth Savile .
Horace Field Parshall ( 9 September 1865 - -12 December 1932 ) was an electrical engineer specialising in rotating electrical machines , railway traction , and electrical distribution .
Helen Douglas Irvine ( born Helen Florence Douglas - Irvine ; 29 February 1880 -- died 1947 ) was a Scottish novelist , historian and translator and was one of the Douglases of Grangemuir .
Henry Robinson Hartley ( 12 November 1777 Southampton -- 24 May 1850 Calais , France ) was an English eccentric and philanthropist .
Jovan Kantul ( Serbian Cyrillic : Јован Кантул , fl . 1592 -- d. 1614 ) , sometimes numbered Jovan II was the Patriarch of Peć , the spiritual leader of the Serbian Orthodox Church , from 1592 until his death in 1614 .
Warren Hudson ( 25 May 1962 -- 16 February 2012 ) was a player in the Canadian Football League .
William Thornton Watson , DSO , MC , DCM ( 10 November 1887 -- 9 September 1961 ) was a New Zealander who served as an officer in the Australian Imperial Force in both World Wars .
Lei Chen ( Chinese : 雷震 ; pinyin : Léi Zhèn ; 1897 - -1979 ) was an early leading figure in the movement to bring fuller democracy to the government of the Republic of China .
Sir Robert Stawell Ball FRS ( 1 July 1840 -- 25 November 1913 ) was an Irish astronomer who founded the screw theory .
Raimundas Čivilis ( 24 November 1959 -- 27 November 2000 ) was a former Lithuanian basketball player , known for his career in Žalgiris Kaunas from 1977 till 1988 .
Paek Son - haeng ( 1848 November -- 1933 ) was a Korean businesswoman known for her massive charitable donations .
Anton Heiller ( 15 September 1923 -- 25 March 1979 ) was an Austrian organist , harpsichordist , composer , and conductor .
Charles Loraine Smith or Charles Loraine ( 1 April 1751 -- 24 August 1835 ) was a sportsman , artist and politician .
Charles J. Burstone ( April 4 , 1928 - February 11 , 2015 ) was an American Orthodontist who was notable for his contributions to biomechanics and force - systems in the field of Orthodontics .
Sachal Sarmast ( 1739 -- 1829 ) ( Sindhi : سچلُ سرمستُ‎ , Urdu : سچل سرمست‎ ) was a Sufi poet from Sindh , Pakistan .
Richard Welton ( 1671/1672 - 22 July 1726 ) was an English Anglican non - juror .
Charlotte von Rothschild ( 13 June 1819 -- 13 March 1884 ) was a German - born British socialite .
Eluned Phillips ( 27 October 1914 -- 10 January 2009 ) was the only woman to win the bardic crown at the National Eisteddfod of Wales twice , a feat she accomplished in 1967 at Bala and 1983 at Llangefni .
Alfredo Bracchi ( 30 December 1897 -- 11 October 1976 ) was a versatile Italian author , whose production ranged from song lyrics to movie scripts .
Tina Lattanzi ( 5 December 1897 -- 25 October 1997 ) was an Italian actress and prominent voice artist , dubbing movie stars .
Rashid Maidin ( 10 October 1917 -- 1 September 2006 ) , sometimes given as Rashid Mahideen , was a senior leader of the Communist Party of Malaya ( CPM ) .
Hubert Aquin ( 24 October 1929 -- 15 March 1977 ) was a Quebec novelist , political activist , essayist , filmmaker and editor .
Anselm Casimir Wambold von Umstadt ( 1582 - -1647 ) was the Archbishop - Elector of Mainz from 1629 to 1647 .
Jonathan Mock Beck ( aka Jon Beck ; 11 November 1935 -- 11 March 2006 , Somerville , Massachusetts ) was an American mathematician , who worked on category theory and algebraic topology .
Subhan Quli Qutb Shah ( 1543 - 1550 ) ( Urdu : سبحان قلی قطب شاہ ) was 7 years old , when he became Sultan of Golconda , after the death of his father Jamsheed Quli Qutb Shah , in 1550 .
Antonio Maria Valsalva ( 17 January 1666 -- 2 February 1723 ) , was an Italian anatomist born in Imola .
Zhu Shijie ( Chinese : 朱世杰 ; pinyin : Zhū Shìjié ; Wade -- Giles : Chu Shih - chieh , 1249 - -1314 ) , courtesy name Hanqing ( 汉卿 ) , pseudonym Songting ( 松庭 ) , was one of the greatest Chinese mathematicians living during the Yuan Dynasty .
Joseph Hodgson ( 1788 - -1869 ) was a British physician and a well - known Quaker .
Archibald James Campbell ( 18 February 1853 -- 11 September 1929 ) was an Australian civil servant in the Victorian , later the Australian federal customs service , as well as an amateur ornithologist .
Mogens Pedersøn ( c. 1583 -- January or February 1623 ) was a Danish instrumentalist and composer .
Agnes Nanogak Goose ( 12 November 1925 -- 5 May 2001 ) was an Inuk artist from Holman ( Ulukhaktok ) , Northwest Territories , Canada .
Franz Joseph Damian Junghanns ( 29 November 1800 , in Stocksberg castle -- 3 December 1875 , in Baden - Baden ) was a Jurist and leader in the Baden Revolution of 1848 .
I Gusti Nyoman Lempad ( 1862?--1978 ) was known as a Balinese stone sculptor and architect ( Undagi in Balinese ) who built the palaces and temples in Ubud and its neighboring villages .
Ewart Morrison ( 7 October 1899 -- 12 May 1985 ) was an English cricketer .
Charles McCabe ( 1915 - -1983 ) was a columnist for the San Francisco Chronicle from the mid-1950s until his death May 1 , 1983 at the age of 68 .
Jodocus Badius ( French : Josse Bade ; Spanish : Jodoco del Badia ; 1462 - -1535 ) , also known as Josse Badius , Jodocus van Asche Badius , and Badius Ascensius , was a pioneer of the printing industry , a renowned grammarian , and a pedagogue .
Octavius Temple ( 1784 - -1834 ) , was Lieutenant Governor of Sierra Leone and Superintendent General of the Liberated Africans Department ( 1833 ) , British soldier and colonial official .
Muhammad of Ghazni ( Persian : محمد غزنوی‎‎ ) ( died 1041 ) was sultan of the Ghaznavid Empire briefly in 1030 , and then later from 1040 to 1041 .
Raj Chandra Bose ( 19 June 1901 -- 31 October 1987 ) was an Indian American mathematician and statistician best known for his work in design theory , finite geometry and the theory of error - correcting codes in which the class of BCH codes is partly named after him .
Abu al - Hakam al - Kirmani ( Arabic : أبو الحكم الكرماني‎ ; d. 1066 CE ) was a prominent philosopher and scholar from the Muslim al - Andalus .
Willy van Hemert ( 29 March 1912 -- 26 June 1993 ) was a Dutch actor and theatre and television director , but is best known as a songwriter who penned two winning Dutch songs for the Eurovision Song Contest .
Julius Gehl ( July 4 , 1869 , Bromberg , Province of Posen - March 1945 , Danzig ) was a German social democratic politician .
Ernst von Grünigen ( born March 23 , 1950 -- June , 1992 ) was a Swiss ski jumper who competed from 1971 to 1977 .
John William Friso , Prince of Orange - Nassau ( Dutch : Johan Willem Friso van Oranje - Nassau ; 14 August 1687 -- 14 July 1711 ) became the titular Prince of Orange in 1702 .
Konstantin Rodko ( 24 August 1908 -- 30 September 1995 ) was a Latvian painter who was based in the United States .
Thomas Simson ( 1696 - -1764 ) was a Scottish medical academic at the University of St Andrews .
Frederick Basil Chubb ( 8 December 1921 -- 8 May 2002 ) was an English and Irish political scientist , author and broadcaster .
George Louis Beer ( July 26 , 1872 -- March 15 , 1920 ) was a renowned American historian of the `` Imperial school '' .
Joseph Baumhauer ( died 22 March 1772 ) was a prominent Parisian ébéniste , one of several of German extraction .
Moses Tyson ( born 1897 , Westmorland ; died 1969 ) , historian and librarian , was keeper of western manuscripts at the John Rylands Library 1927 - 1935 and from 1935 to 1965 librarian of the Manchester University Library .
Alfred Short ( 1882 -- 24 August 1938 , London ) was a British trades unionist and Labour politician , Member of Parliament ( MP ) for Wednesbury from 1918 to 1931 , and for Doncaster from 1935 until 1938 .
Guido de Bres ( also known as Guido de Bray , Guy de Bray and Guido de Brès , 1522 -- 31 May 1567 ) was a Walloon pastor and theologian , a student of John Calvin and Theodore Beza in Geneva .
James Augustus Grant , CB , CSI , FRS , FRGS ( 11 April 1827 -- 11 February 1892 ) was a Scottish explorer of eastern equatorial Africa .
George Mikhailovich , Count Brasov ( Russian : Георгий Михайлович , граф Брасов ; 6 August ( O.S. 24 July ) 1910 -- 21 July 1931 ) was a Russian noble and a descendant of the House of Romanov through a morganatic line .
Major - General Sir John Braithwaite , 1st Baronet ( 3 February 1739 - 16 August 1803 ) was Commander - in - Chief of the Madras Army .
Victor Rosellini ( 1915 - -2003 ) was a Seattle restaurateur , and president of the National Restaurant Association and the Restaurant Association of the State of Washington .
George Brookshaw ( c. 1751 - 1823 ) , also known as G. Brown , was a notable English painter and illustrator from London .
Alain Mimoun ( 1 January 1921 -- 27 June 2013 ) was an Algerian - born French long - distance runner who competed in track events , cross - country running and the marathon .
Edward Holme ( 17 February 1770 -- 28 November 1847 ) was an English physician and supporter of learned societies .
Henry Yates Thompson ( 15 December 1838 -- 8 July 1928 ) was a British newspaper proprietor and collector of illuminated manuscripts .
Francesco Rizzoli ( 11 July 1809 - 24 May 1880 ) was an Italian politician , surgeon and physician , considered one of the fathers of modern orthopedics .
Brita Sofia Hesselius ( 1801 - 1866 ) was a Swedish daguerreotype photographer .
Justice Eugene Wilfred Jayewardene , KC ( Sinhala:ඉයුජින් විල්ෆ්‍රඩ් ජයවර්ධන ; 11 June 1874 -- 23 November 1932 ) was a Ceylonese ( Sri Lankan ) judge , lawyer and politician .
James Tyson ( 8 April 1819 -- 4 December 1898 ) was an Australian pastoralist .
Henry Wardle ( 1832 -- 16 February 1892 ) was a British brewer and Liberal politician who sat in the House of Commons from 1885 to 1892 .
Kevin Grose ( 18 June 1954 -- 27 November 2012 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Collingwood in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
William George Howard , 8th Earl of Carlisle ( 23 February 1808 -- 29 March 1889 ) was an English clergyman and peer .
Maurice Frigara ( 2 July 1874 -- 27 January 1955 ) was a French conductor of Corsican descent , mainly active in the opera house .
Anne Szumigalski , SOM ( 3 January 1922 -- 22 April 1999 ) was a Canadian poet .
Samuel Malthouse ( 13 October 1857 -- 7 February 1931 ) was an English cricketer who played for Derbyshire between 1890 and 1895 .
Oswald Taylor Brown OBE , FRCP(Glasg ) , FRCP(Ed ) ( 11 October 1916 -- 26 March 2006 ) was a Scottish consultant physician in geriatric medicine based in Dundee from 1951 until 1979 .
Breasal Madden ( died 1745 ) , Chief of the Name , from 1727 to 1745 .
Konrad the Curly ( Polish : Konrad Kędzierzawy ; b. ca . 1198 -- d. Czerwony Kosciol , 4 September 1213 ) , was a Polish prince member of the Piast dynasty in his Silesian branch .
Sir William Wyndham , 1st Baronet ( ca . 1632 -- 29 October 1683 ) of Orchard Wyndham , Somerset , was Member of Parliament for Somerset in 1656 and twice for Taunton in 1659 and 1660 .
Nicolaus or Mikołaj Szyszkowski ( 1590 - -1643 ) of Ostoja coat of arms was a Prince - bishop of Warmia from 1633 til his death in 1643 .
Jean - Jules Allasseur ( 13 June 1818 -- 1903 ) was a French sculptor , a pupil of Pierre - Jean David called David d'Angers at the École des Beaux - Arts , Paris , who produced portrait sculptures , memorial allegories and decorative architectural sculpture for official commissions under the Second Empire .
Victor Mishcon , Baron Mishcon , QC , DL ( 14 August 1915 -- 27 January 2006 ) was a leading British solicitor and a Labour politician .
Albert C. Sutphin , also known as Al Sutphin and `` the man in the red necktie '' , ( 1895 - -1974 ) was a sports promoter and businessman in Cleveland , Ohio .
José Barona remained at San Juan Capistrano , where he ministered to the natives until his death on August 4 , 1831 .
José Pedro Braga , OBE ( Chinese : 布力架 ; 1871 - -1944 Macau ) was the manager of the Hong Kong Telegraph between 1902 and 1910 .
Bryan Charnley ( 1949 - -1991 ) was a British artist most famous for a series of self portraits he painted examining his schizophrenia and the effect of the different medications he used to control the condition .
Pascal Antoine Fiorella or Pasquale Antonio , comte Fiorella ( 7 February 1752 -- 3 March 1818 ) became a French general officer in the French Revolutionary Wars and led a brigade during Napoleon Bonaparte 's famous campaign in Italy in 1796 .
Edward Deering Mansfield ( August 17 , 1801 --October 27 , 1880 ) , was an American author .
May Theilgaard Watts ( 1893 -- 20 August 1975 ) was an American writer , illustrator , and teacher .
Helmut Volz ( German : ( fɔlts ) ; 1 August 1911 in Göppingen -- 23 October 1978 ) was a German experimental nuclear physicist who worked on the German nuclear energy project during World War II . In the latter years of World War II , he became a professor at Erlangen University .
Empress Kong ( 孔皇后 , personal name unknown ) ( d. 934 ) , formally Empress Ai ( 哀皇后 , `` the lamentable empress '' ) , was an empress of the Chinese Five Dynasties and Ten Kingdoms Period state Later Tang .
John Kernan Mullen Irish - American businessman and philanthropist , 11 June 1847 - 9 August 1929 .
Richard Towgood ( c.1595 - -1683 ) was an English royalist churchman , Dean of Bristol from 1667 .
Amy Watkins ( 1973 - -1999 ) was a social worker from Topeka , Kansas , who was murdered while walking down the street on March 8 , 1999 , in Brooklyn , New York .
Edward Crankshaw ( 3 January 1909 -- 30 November 1984 ) , was a British writer , translator and commentator on Soviet affairs .
Jean Adebambo ( 1 July 1962 -- 15 January 2009 ) was a British black caribbean singer , best known for songs in the lovers rock genre .
Rosetta Howard ( 1914 -- 1974 ) was an American blues singer , who recorded in the 1930s and 1940s .
Kenneth Royce Gandley ( 1920 - -1997 ) was an English thriller writer who also wrote under name Ken Royce , and the pseudonym Oliver Jacks .
Ma Yuehan ( Chinese : 马约翰 , 1883 - -1966 ) was a pioneer in physical education and modern Chinese sports .
Hans Rudolph ( November 17 , 1903 -- February 1994 ) , was a pioneer in the development of respiratory equipment and supplies .
Adam Gerard Mappa ( Tournai , 25 November 1754 -- Barneveld , New York , 15 April 1828 ) was a Dutch Patriot and active colonel in a local militia ( in Dutch exercitiegenootschap ) .
Tom Dundee ( 1946 - -2006 ) was a singer / songwriter born in Chicago , Illinois , United States .
Hector McLean ( 1864 -- January 1888 ) was an Australian born rower who rowed in the Boat Race and won Silver Goblets at Henley Royal Regatta .
Laurie Murphy ( 10 September 1899 -- 20 July 1980 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Collingwood and North Melbourne in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Echu Tirmcharna mac Fergusso ( died ca . 556 ) was a king of Connacht from the Uí Briúin branch of the Connachta .
John Edward Carew ( c. 1785 -- 1 December 1868 ) was a notable Irish sculptor during the 19th century .
Antonio Maria Cagiano de Azevedo ( 14 December 1797 -- 13 January 1867 ) was a Catholic Cardinal and held a number of significant legal positions within the Catholic Church during the 19th century .
Štěpán Kodeda ( 5 February 1988 -- 30 March 2015 ) was a Czech orienteering competitor , and twice junior world champion .
William Blaisdell ( 1865 - 1931 ) was an American actor of both stage and screen .
Wim Mager ( Rotterdam , 26 September 1940 - Silvolde , 23 March 2008 ) was a Dutch photographer who is mainly known for founding the Apenheul Primate Park near Apeldoorn of which he was the director until 1997 .
George Shelvocke ( baptised 1 April 1675 -- 30 November 1742 ) was an English Royal Navy officer and later privateer who in 1723 wrote A Voyage Round the World by Way of the Great South Sea based on his exploits .
Sir George Wharton , 1st Baronet ( 4 April 1617 -- 12 August 1681 ) was an English Royalist soldier and astrologer , also known as a poet .
William An tAb Caoch Bourke , 20th Mac William Iochtar , died 1593 .
Albert Fennell ( 29 March 1920 in Chiswick -- 17 April 1988 ) was a British film and television producer .
John Blackall M.D. , FRCP ( 24 December 1771 -- 10 January 1860 ) was an English physician .
Piaras Feiritéar ( Irish pronunciation : ( ˈpʲiəɾˠəsˠ fʲɛɾʲiˈtʲeːɾˠ ) ; 1600 ? -- 1653 ) was an Irish poet .
Paul Alfred Rapp ( 9 February 1933 -- 25 July 2011 ) was a German Economist and a regional politician .
Peder Henrik Kristian Zahrtmann , known as Kristian Zahrtmann , ( 31 March 1843 - 22 June 1917 ) was a Danish painter .
Stephen Robert Dunlop ( 25 November 1960 -- 15 May 2008 ) was a Northern Irish motorcycle racer , the younger brother of fellow road racer , the late Joey Dunlop , and like Joey he died after a crash while racing .
Adolf Fischhof ( Hungarian : Fischhof Adolf ) ( 8 December 1816 -- 23 March 1893 ) was a Hungarian - Austrian writer and politician of Jewish descent .
Isaac Mustafin ( Russian : Исаак Савельевич Мустафин ) ( 1908 - -1968 ) was a Russian chemist and a doctor of chemical sciences .
Pierre Simon ( 1 December 1808 -- 12 December 1881 ) , later known as Paul Simon , was a French archetier or bowmaker .
Võ Duy Dương ( 武維楊 ; 1827 - -1866 ) , also Thiên Hộ Dương ( 千戶楊 ) was a Vietnamese warlord who after the submission of the Vietnamese government to the French in 1862 continued to fight against the French ( 1862 - 1866 ) in the wetlands of Đồng Tháp Mười , where he died of disease .
Jerzy Górski ( October 27 , 1929 -- May 1997 ) is a Polish sprint canoer who competed in the late 1950s .
Sir Raleigh Grey KBE CMG CVO ( 24 March 1860 -- 10 January 1936 ) was a pioneer British coloniser of Southern Rhodesia who played an important part in the early government of the colony .
Saint Agnes of Assisi , O.S.C. , ( 1197/1198 -- 16 November 1253 ) was the younger sister of Saint Clare of Assisi and one of the first abbesses of the Order of Poor Ladies .
General William Belford ( 1709 - -1780 ) was an English artillery officer .
Arthur Sowden ( 6 April 1878 -- 24 December 1954 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Melbourne in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Ren Xun ( Chinese : 任薰 ; Wade -- Giles : Jen Hsün ; ca . 1835 - -1893 ) was a Chinese painter during the Qing Dynasty .
Zacharias Chrysopolitanus ( d. c. 1155 ) , also known as Zachary of Besançon , was a biblical scholar of the Premonstratensian Order from Besançon ( Chrysopolis ) .
Nalan Xingde ( simplified Chinese : 纳兰性德 ; traditional Chinese : 納蘭性德 ; Wade -- Giles : Na - lan Hsing - te ; 1655 - -1685 ) , courtesy name Rongruo ( 容若 ) , was a Qing dynasty Chinese poet , famous for his ci poetry .
Des Meagher ( 7 March 1944 -- 9 March 2011 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Hawthorn in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Rev. Michael Buckworth Bailey M.A. ( 10 April 1827 - 6 December 1899 ) A minister of the Church of England .
Sir William Edge , 1st Baronet ( 21 November 1880 -- 18 December 1948 ) was a British Liberal , later National Liberal politician and businessman .
Karma Phuntsok Namgyal ( Tibetan : ཀར་མ་ཕུན་ཚོགས་རྣམ་རྒྱལ་ , Wylie : Kar - ma Phun - tshogs Rnam - rgyal ) ( 1587 -- March 1620 ) was a king of Tibet who ruled from 1618 to 1620 .
William Newmarch ( 28 January 1820 -- 23 March 1882 ) was an English banker , economist and statistician .
K. Devasahayam ( Telugu : దేవసహాయము అయ్యగారు ; 5 June 1916 -- 30 January 1992 ) was President of the Andhra Evangelical Lutheran Church from 1965 to 1969 .
Gunvor Galtung Haavik ( 7 October 1912 -- 5 August 1977 ) was a Norwegian employee of the Norwegian Ministry of Foreign Affairs who was arrested on 27 January 1977 after being betrayed by Oleg Gordievsky and charged with espionage on behalf of the Soviet Union and treason .
Beatrix of Brandenburg ( died : 22 September 1314 in Wismar ) was the first wife of Lord Henry II `` the Lion '' of Mecklenburg ( 1266 - 1329 ) , whom she married in 1292 at Stargard Castle .
Isaac Thomas ( 4 November 1784 - 2 February 1859 ) , was an American politician representing Tennessee in the United States House of Representatives .
Leonardo Navigajoso ( died 1260 ) was a Venetian nobleman and second Latin ruler of the island of Lemnos in Greece .
Richard Edgcumbe , 2nd Baron Edgcumbe PC ( 2 August 1716 -- 10 May 1761 ) was a British nobleman and politician .
Fikret Arıcan ( 17 July 1912 -- 1994 ) was the Chairman of the Türkiye Süper Ligi team Fenerbahçe between 1984 - -86 .
Maurice Ronald MacNab , born in Hythe , Kent on 6 May 1902 -- 12 April 1962 , was an English cricketer .
Flor Peeters ( Baron Peeters ) ( born 4 July 1903 in Tielen , died 4 July 1986 in Mechelen ) was an important Belgian composer , organist and teacher .
Lucy Wills , MA ( Cantab ) , LRCP , MB BS ( Lond ) ( 10 May 1888 -- 26 April 1964 ) was a leading English haematologist .
Paul Matteoli ( 7 November 1929 -- 12 December 1988 ) was a French cyclist who was active on the road and track between 1949 and 1956 .
Jack Merriott RI , ROI , RSMA , RWS ( 15 November 1901 -- 1968 ) was an English author , artist , and poster designer famous for his artworks produced for British Railways and the General Post Office .
Pedro Ponce de León the Elder ( died 1352 ) was a Castilian nobleman , grandson of King Alfonso IX of León .
Nicolas - Sébastien Adam ( 22 March 1705 -- 27 March 1778 ) , also called `` Adam the Younger '' , was a French sculptor working in the Neoclassical style .
Karl - Heinz Reincke ( 28 May 1925 -- 13 July 2011 ) was a German - born actor , long - based in Vienna .
Joseph Bradish ( 28 November 1672 -- 12 July 1700 ) was a pirate in the company of Captain Kidd .
John Washington ( 1633 - -1677 ) was an English Virginia planter and politician .
Adolf Heyduk ( 6 June 1835 -- 6 February 1923 ) was a distinguished Czech poet and writer .
Lars Brandstrup ( 13 April 1913 -- 25 January 1997 ) was a Norwegian gallerist .
B. Muriel Bristol - Roach ( 21 April 1888 -- 15 March 1950 ) , Ph.D. , was a scientist working in the field of alga biology who worked at the Rothamsted Experimental Station in 1919 .
Richard Wright Procter ( 1816 - -1881 ) was an English barber , poet and author .
Ralph Townsend ( 27 November 1900 -- 25 January 1976 ) was an American author , consul and political activist noted for his opposition to the entry of the United States into World War II . Townsend was born in North Carolina and educated in New York .
Nichiō ( 日奥 , 1565 -- 1630 ) was a Nichiren Buddhist who founded the Fuju - fuse subsect .
Dame Flora MacLeod of MacLeod , DBE ( 3 February 1878 -- 4 November 1976 ) was the 28th chief of Clan MacLeod .
Willy Stöwer ( 22 May 1864 -- 31 May 1931 ) was a German artist , illustrator and author during the Imperial Period .
Jane Bruce ( 1847 or 1848 -- 30 November 1907 ) was a Canadian teacher .
Jane West ( born Iliffe ) ( 1758 - -1852 ) , who published as Prudentia Homespun and Mrs. West , was an English novelist , poet , playwright , and writer of conduct literature and educational tracts .
Mysore Srinivas ( 1943 -- 16 October 1995 ) , known by his stage name Thoogudeepa Srinivas , was an Indian film actor who acted in Kannada films .
SS - Scharführer Herbert Floss or Herbert Floß ( 25 August 1912 -- 22 October 1943 ) served as acting commander of the Sobibor extermination camp during the Holocaust in Poland .
Dantidurga ( 735 - -756 CE ) , also known as Dantivarman or Dantidurga II was the founder of the Rashtrakuta Empire of Manyakheta .
George Ross , 11th Lord Ross of Halkhead ( died April 1682 ) , was a Scottish nobleman and soldier .
Richard Maitland , 4th Earl of Lauderdale ( 20 June 1653 , Haltoun House -- 1695 , Paris , France ) was a Scottish politician .
Jan Kiszka ( 1552 - -1592 ) was a politician , magnate , patron , and benefactor of Polish brethren in the 16th century Polish - Lithuanian Commonwealth .
Joseph Escapa ( c. 1572 - -1662 ) served in the rabbinate of İzmir .
Frederick William , Prince of Nassau - Weilburg ( Friedrich Wilhelm ; 25 October 1768 , The Hague -- 9 January 1816 , Weilburg ) was a ruler of Nassau - Weilburg .
Anwar Solangi ( 1944 - -2008 ) was a Pakistani television and radio artist .
Daniel Ozmo ( born 1912 in Olovo , died 1942 in Jasenovac concentration camp ) was a Yugoslav Jewish painter and printmaker .
Pádraig Ághas ( died 22 December 1966 ) was an Irish independent politician and schoolteacher .
Nikolaus Gerhaert ( c.1420 -- 11 June 1473 ) , also known as Nikolaus Gerhaert van Leyden , was a sculptor of Dutch origin , although aside from his sculptures , few details are known of his life .
Rabbi Hillel Poisic ( 15.1.1881 Zlatopol , Ukraine -- 1953 Tel Aviv , Israel ) was a communal worker and Torah scholar .
Nasir ad - Din Mahmud ( or Mahmud II ) was the Zengid Emir of Mossul 1219 - -1234 .
Bernhard Eriksson ( 19 April 1878 -- 18 April 1952 ) was a Swedish social democratic politician .
Peder Jönsson ( died 1640 ) , was a Swedish hunter and fisherman from Söderköping , who was executed for having confessed to sexual intercourse with a Sjörået ( a lake - nymph ; a mythical female creature of the lake ) .
Piotr Tomicki ( 1464 -- 19 October 1535 ) was a Roman Catholic Bishop of Przemyśl and Poznań , Archbishop of Kraków , Vice - Chancellor of the Crown , and Royal Secretary .
Charles d’Orville Pilkington Jackson ARSA , FRBS , FRSA ( 11 October 1887 -- 20 September 1973 ) was a British sculptor prominent in Scotland in the 20th century .
Maximilien Winter ( 1871 - -1935 ) was a French philosopher of mathematics .
Jürgen Henning Illies ( 14 March 1924 -- 2 August 1982 ) was a German geologist expert in taphrogenesis ( i.e. rift formation ) .
Gabriel Gifford OSB ( also known as Dom Gabriel of St Mary or French : Gabriel de Sainte - Marie ) ( 1554 -- 11 April 1629 ) was an English Roman Catholic Benedictine monk who became Archbishop of Reims .
Nguyễn Tường Tam ( Cẩm Giàng , Hải Dương 25 July 1906 - Saigon , 7 July 1963 ) better known by his pen - name Nhất Linh was a Vietnamese writer , editor and publisher in colonial Hanoi .
Pieter Snyers or Peter Snijers ( first name also written as : ' Peeter ' and nickname ' De Heilige ' or ' The Holy One ' ) ( 30 March 1681 - 4 May 1752 ) was a Flemish art collector , painter , draughtsman and engraver who worked in a wide variety of genres .
Yoshinao Nakada ( 中田喜直 , Shibuya , Tokyo , 1 August 1923 -- 3 May 2000 ) was a Japanese composer .
Edward Morecroft ( died 1580 ) was a Canon of Windsor from 1560 to 1580
Matthew Raine ( 1760 - -1811 ) was an English schoolmaster and cleric .
Daniel Thomas Egerton ( 1797 - 1842 ) , was a British landscape painter , Egerton was one of the original members of the Society of British Artists , where he exhibited in the years 1824 to 1829 , and in 1838 to 1840 .
Lucas Fernández de Piedrahita ( 1624-March 29 , 1688 ) was a Roman Catholic prelate who served as the Bishop of Panamá ( 1676 - 1688 ) and the Bishop of Santa Marta ( 1668 - 1676 ) .
Major Sir George Gipps ( 1791 -- 28 February 1847 ) was Governor of the colony of New South Wales , Australia , for eight years , between 1838 and 1846 .
Thích Thiên - Ân ( 釋天恩 ) ( September 1926 - November 1980 ) was an influential teacher and Buddhist monk of Vietnamese Thiền ( Zen ) Buddhism and was active in the United States from 1966 to 1980 .
Eleanor Palmer ( died 29 February 1558 ) was an English philanthropist who established a charity to help the poor of Chipping Barnet and Kentish Town .
Milorad Rajović ( Serbian Cyrillic : Милорад Рајовић ; 13 May 1955 -- 12 January 2016 ) was a Serbian footballer .
Stanislaus Mink von Wennsshein ( also Wenusheim , Winusheim ) was the pseudonym of Johann Just Winkelmann ( 1620 - 1699 ) , under which he introduced a famous mnemonic system known as the major system ( also called phonetic system or phonetic mnemonic system ) , which is over 300 years old and is used for memorizing numbers .
Sophia Julia Woolf ( born 1831 , d. 1903 ) was an English composer known for songs and opera .
Sam Kahn ( 15 December 1911 -- 25 August 1987 ) was a South African Communist and MP from 1949 to 1952 , for one of the constituencies representing African voters .
Carlos Frederick MacDonald , M.D. ( August 29 , 1845 -- May 29 , 1926 ) was a psychiatrist , and the chairman of the New York State Commission in Lunacy from 1880 to 1896 .
Anna Komnene Doukaina ( died 4 January 1286 ) , known in French as Agnes , was Princess - consort of the Principality of Achaea in 1258 - -1278 .
Albert Ernest Archer ( died 1949 ) was a Canadian physician and political activist .
Coert Steynberg ( 7 January 1905 -- 28 July 1982 ) was a renowned South African sculptor who worked in stone , marble , bronze , copper and wood .
Robert Chalmers , 1st Baron Chalmers , GCB , PC ( 18 August 1858 -- 17 November 1938 ) , was a British civil servant , and a Pali and Buddhist scholar .
Thomas Lanquet ( or Lanket ) ( 1521 - -1545 ) was an English chronicler .
Antonio Piccinni ( 1846- January , 1920 ) was an Italian painter , mainly of watercolors .
Sir Henry le Scrope ( b. in or before 1268 - 7 September 1336 ) was an English lawyer , and Chief Justice of the King 's Bench for two periods between 1317 and 1330 .
Domenico Poggini ( 1520 - -1590 ) was an Italian sculptor , engraver , medallist , goldsmith , and poet .
James Livingston , 1st Earl of Callendar ( c. 1590s -- 1674 ) , army officer who fought on the Royalist side in the Wars of the Three Kingdoms .
John Streater ( died 1687 ) was an English soldier , political writer and printer .
Opoku Ware I ( 1700 - -1750 ) was an Oyoko king or Asantehene - the ruler of the Ashanti - in the now - disbanded Ashanti Confederacy which occupied parts of what is now Ghana .
Paul Vacher ( pronounced : ( pɔl vaʃe ) ) ( died 1975 ) was a French perfumer .
Hugo Neumann ( 8 May 1882 -- 4 September 1962 ) was a German jurist , politician of the Free City of Danzig and writer .
Gilbert Vaughn Hemsley , Jr. ( 1936 - -1983 ) was a noted United States lighting designer and teacher of lighting design .
Frank Sparrow ( 1 July 1927 -- 31 December 2000 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played for East Perth , Swan Districts and West Perth in the WANFL during the 1940s and 1950s .
Sir Ralph Sandwich ( 1235 - -1308 ) ( also known as Ralph de Sandwich and Ralph of Sandwich ) , of Dene ( in Margate ) , Ham , and Ripple , Kent , Winchfield , Hampshire , etc . , was an English administrator and justice .
Stephen Moore , 2nd Earl Mount Cashell ( 19 March 1770 -- 27 October 1822 ) , styled Lord Kilworth between 1781 and 1790 , was an Anglo - Irish politician .
George Syncellus ( Greek : Γεώργιος Σύγκελλος ; died after 810 ) was a Byzantine chronicler and ecclesiastic .
John Scandrett Harford , FRS ( 8 October 1785 -- 16 April 1866 ) was a British banker , benefactor and abolitionist .
Kannavath Sankaran Nambiar ( c. 1760 -- 27 November 1801 ) was the prime minister or Sarvadikaryakar of Pazhassi Raja .
Erich Ebermayer ( 14 September 1900 -- 22 September 1970 ) was a German writer who wrote a number of plays , novels and articles .
Harold Edwin Hurst ( 1 January 1880 -- 7 December 1978 ) was a British hydrologist from Leicester .
Bismillah Khan ( Urdu : استاد بسم اللہ خان صاحب‎ ; 21 March 1913 -- 21 August 2006 ) , often referred to by the honorific title Ustad , was an Indian musician credited with popularizing the shehnai , a subcontinental wind instrument of the oboe class .
Isabella Colonna ( 1513 - 1570 ) was an Italian noblewoman , a member of the Colonna family .
Giampiero Albertini ( 20 December 1927 -- 14 May 1991 ) was an Italian actor , voice actor and TV personality .
Olimpia Ana Pía Sebastiani ( 27 February 1925 -- 26 July 2015 ) was an Argentine pianist and composer .
Sir Michael Kerry KCB QC MA ( 5 August 1923 -- 11 May 2012 ) was the holder of the official titles of Her Majesty 's Procurator General and Treasury Solicitor from 1980 to 1984 .
Juan Hernández Giménez ( 1914 - -2006 ) was an aviator and informant Spanish for the French Resistance .
Romana Calligaris ( 15 December 1924 -- 21 April 2002 ) was an Italian freestyle swimmer who won 15 national titles between 1947 and 1953 .
Shivaji Bhonsle ( Marathi ( ʃiʋaˑɟiˑ bʱoˑs(ə)leˑ ) ; c. 1627/1630 -- 3 April 1680 ) , also known as Chhatrapati Shivaji Maharaj , was an Indian warrior king and a member of the Bhonsle Maratha clan .
Philip D. Coombs was the Washington State Archivist under Secretary of State Ralph Munroe and then under Secretary of State Sam Reed from October 1999 through his sudden death in July 2001 .
William Coffey VC DCM ( 5 August 1829 -- 13 July 1875 ) , born in Knocklong , County Limerick , was an Irish recipient of the Victoria Cross , the highest and most prestigious award for gallantry in the face of the enemy that can be awarded to British and Commonwealth forces .
Ludwik Sempoliński , real name Bohdan Kierski ( 18 August 1899 -- 17 April 1981 ) was a Polish film actor .
Lemuel Abbott ( ca . 1730 -- April 1776 ) was an English clergyman and poet .
Joshua Jeays died on 11 March 1881 in Brisbane and is buried in Toowong Cemetery .
Wentworth Dillon , 4th Earl of Roscommon ( c. 1633 -- 18 January 1685 ) , was an English poet .
K. Krishnamurthy ( 22 October 1915 - 6 March 2011 ) was an Indian writer , publisher and political activist .
Sara Benetowa , later known as Sula Benet ( 1903 - -1982 ) , was a Polish anthropologist of the 20th century who studied Polish and Judaic customs and traditions .
Rainulf Drengot ( also Ranulph , Ranulf , or Rannulf ; died June 1045 ) was a Norman adventurer and mercenary in southern Italy .
Václav David ( 23 September 1910 , Studený , Bohemia - 5 January 1996 ) is a Czechoslovak diplomat , he was Czechoslovak foreign minister from 31 January 1953 to 8 April 1968 .
Princess Maria Anna Victoria of Savoy ( 11 September 1683 -- 11 October 1763 ) was the daughter of Prince Louis Thomas of Savoy , Count of Soissons , and Uranie de La Cropte de Beauvais .
John Warner Barber ( February 2 , 1798 -- June 1885 ) was an American engraver whose books of state , national , and local history featured his vivid illustrations , said to have caught the flavor and appearance of city , town , and countryside scenes in his day .
Roberto Ubaldini ( 1581 -- 22 April 1635 ) was a bishop and cardinal of the Catholic Church .
Andy Pattison ( 2 November 1885 -- 12 June 1952 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Carlton , Fitzroy and Richmond in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Morris Cargill CD ( 10 June 1914 -- 8 April 2000 , Kingston ) was a Jamaican lawyer , businessman , planter , journalist and novelist .
Valentin Voss ( 27 August 1880 -- 23 June 1964 ) was a Norwegian lawyer and civil servant .
Jeanie ( Jenny ) Cameron ( 1695?--1773 ? or 1724?--1786 ? ) was a hero of the Jacobite risings in Scotland under Bonnie Prince Charlie in 1745 .
Ivan Broz ( 21 January 1852 -- 25 December 1893 ) was a Croatian linguist and literary historian .
Jean - Pierre Ponnelle ( 19 February 1932 -- 11 August 1988 ) was a noted French opera director .
Roy Allen ( 1918 - -1991 ) was an American , born in the north Philadelphia neighborhood of Olney .
Tan Sri Datin Sri Cempaka Kontek Kamariah Ahmad ( 5 August 1911 - 17 August 2006 ) scored many `` firsts '' for women in the co - operative movement , education and politics in Malaysia .
Michal Har'el née Herison ( 1931 - 2012 ) , was born in Jerusalem and became the second Miss Israel , a women 's rights activist and one of three lifetime honorary presidents of Women 's International Zionist Organization .
Theo van Wijngaarden ( 27 February 1874 , Rotterdam -- 4 November 1952 , Voorburg ) was a Dutch art forger .
John Moat ( 11 September 1936 -- 16 September 2014 ) was a British poet , and co - founder , with John Fairfax , of the Arvon Foundation in 1968 .
Edward Ash Hadow ( 18 April 1831 -- 11 August 1866 ) was an English Chemist .
The Hon . Dr. John Reginald Garcia Valarino MB , ChB , better known as Reggie Valarino , ( 9 June 1941 -- 13 March 2009 ) was a Gibraltarian doctor and politician .
David Friday ( 1876 - -1945 ) president of the U.S. state of Michigan 's Michigan Agricultural College ( now Michigan State University ) from 1922 to 1923 .
Wirjono Prodjodikoro ( 15 June 1903 -- April 1985 ) was the head justice of the Indonesian Supreme Court from 1952 to 1966 .
Taichleach Ua Dubhda , King of Uí Fiachrach Muaidhe , died 1192 .
Jean - Claude Pirotte ( 20 October 1939 -- 24 May 2014 ) was a Belgian writer , poet and painter .
Thomas Sinton , JP ( February 1826 -- 20 August 1887 ) was an Irish industrialist and magistrate .
Mikołaj Ostroróg ( 1593 - -1651 ) was a Polish - Lithuanian szlachcic ( nobleman ) , politician and general .
Ernst Hinterberger ( 17 October 1931 -- 14 May 2012 ) was an Austrian writer of novels , particularly detective novels , plays and successful sitcoms .
Johann Georg Bergmüller ( 15 April 1688 -- 2 April 1762 ) was a painter , particularly of frescoes , of the Baroque .
Abdelaziz Meziane Belfqih ( 1944 - -9 May 2010 ) was a Moroccan civil servant and senior advisor of king Mohammed VI .
Wang Yaowu ( Chinese : 王耀武 ; pinyin : Wáng Yàowŭ , 1904 - -1968 ) was a high - ranking KMT general and the Governor of Shandong Province who successfully fought against both the Imperial Japanese Army and the Chinese Communists .
Franz Werner von Tamm ( 1658 - -1724 ) was a German Baroque painter who travelled to and worked in Italy .
Carl Albert Unbehaun ( 1851 -- 5 February 1924 ) was an electrical engineer in South Australia .
Mihran Apikyan ( Armenian : Միհրան Աբիկյան ; 1855 , Istanbul - 1938 , Istanbul ) was an Armenian and Turkish writer and educator of Armenian descent .
Rabbi Mendel Hess ( March 17 , 1807 , Lengsfeld ( now Stadtlengsfeld ) , Saxe - Weimar - September 21 , 1871 , Eisenach ) was a German rabbi .
Carlo Garbieri ( ca . 1600 - 1649 ) was an Italian painter of the early Baroque period .
Valentin Schindler ( 14 February 1543 -- 11 June 1604 ) was a Lutheran Hebraist and professor of the University of Wittenberg , where he was an important teacher of the Hebrew language .
Squadron Leader John Noel Dowland GC ( 6 November 1914 -- 13 January 1942 ) was awarded the George Cross , as was civilian armament instructor Leonard Henry Harrison , for his gallantry in defusing a bomb which had fallen on the grain ship SS Kildare in Immingham docks on 11 February 1940 .
Tierno Bokar ( Fula : Cerno Bokar ) , full name Tierno Bokar Saalif Tall ( 1875 - -1939 ) , was a Malian mystic , Sufi sage , and a Muslim spiritual teacher of the early twentieth century famous for his message of religious tolerance and universal love .
Berthe Qvistgaard ( 11 August 1910 -- 24 October 1999 ) was a Danish stage and film actress , and winner of the prestigious Tagea Brandt Rejselegat award in 1965 .
Le Yanwei ( 樂彥瑋 ) ( died 676 ) , courtesy name Degui ( 德珪 ) , was an official of the Chinese dynasty Tang Dynasty , serving briefly as chancellor during the reign of Emperor Gaozong .
William Woodfall ( 7 February 1746 -- 1803 ) was an English printer and publisher in the 18th century .
Brigadier Arthur Gordon Matthew CBE DSO ( 22 December 1898 -- 6 October 1947 ) was a British Royal Artillery officer who served in the First World War and the Second World War .
August Spångberg ( 29 March 1893 - 19 June 1987 ) was a Swedish labor politician .
Dilgo Khyentse Rinpoche ( Tibetan : དིལ་མགོ་མཁྱེན་བརྩེ་ , Wylie : dil mgo mkhyen brtse ) ( c. 1910 -- 28 September 1991 ) was a Vajrayana master , scholar , poet , teacher , and head of the Nyingma school of Tibetan Buddhism from 1987 to 1991 .
Arthur Rex Knight , ( 9 May 1903 -- 9 March 1963 ) was born in Wilcannia , New South Wales in Australia .
Eduardo Armstrong Toro ( 24 January 1851 - 19 June 1895 ) was Mayor of Ponce , Puerto Rico , from 1894 to 1895 .
Margrethe von der Lühe ( 1741 - 1826 ) was a Danish courtier ;
Corneille de Lyon ( early 16th century - 8 November 1575 ( buried ) ) ) was a Dutch painter of portraits who was active in Lyon , France from 1533 until his death .
John Colley Nixon ( died 1818 ) was an English merchant and amateur artist .
Robert Charnock ( or Chernock ) ( c. 1663 -- 18 March 1696 ) was an English academic and Jacobite conspirator .
Ioannis Koutsis ( Greek : Ιωάννης Κούτσης , 1860 - 1953 ) was a Greek painter who was a member of the Munich School Greek art movement of the 19th century .
Thomas Bardwell ( 1704 - 9 Sept 1767 ) was an English portrait and figure painter , art copyist , and writer .
Nicholas John Brown ( 9 October 1838 -- 22 September 1903 ) was a pastoralist and politician in colonial Tasmania , a Speaker of the Tasmanian House of Assembly .
Stuart Frank Doyle ( 1 December 1887 -- 1945 ) , better known as Stuart F. Doyle , was an Australian radio and theatrical entrepreneur .
Allen Hughes ( 28 December 1921 -- 16 November 2009 ) was an American dance and music critic .
Laurent Catellier ( 5 September 1839 -- 17 January 1918 ) was a Canadian physician and professor .
Arnold Silverstone , Baron Ashdown ( 28 September 1911 -- 24 July 1977 ) was a British life peer .
Michael of Cesena ( Michele di Cesena or Michele Fuschi ) ( c. 1270 -- 29 November 1342 ) was an Italian Franciscan , general of that Order , and theologian .
Alessandro Moreschi ( 11 November 1858 -- 21 April 1922 ) was a castrato singer of the late 19th century and the only castrato to make solo recordings .
Pak Se - yong ( 1902 - -1989 ) was a North Korean poet and politician , best known for writing the lyrics of `` Aegukka '' , the national anthem of North Korea .
Jacques Alexis de Verteuil ( 26 March 1726 -- 24 December 1793 ) was a French general and chevalier of the Order of the Holy Spirit ( 1770 ) .
Faisal bin Turki I bin Abdulaziz Al Saud ( Arabic : فيصل بن تركي الأول بن عبد العزيز آل سعود‎ , Faisal bin Turkī l-ʾAwwal bin ʿAbd al-ʿAzīz Āl Saʿūd ) ( 1918 - -1968 ) , was the eldest son of Turki I bin Abdulaziz Al Saud .
Johan Fredrik Eckersberg ( 16 June 1822 -- 13 July 1870 ) was a Norwegian painter most noted for his landscapes .
Alfréd Hajós ( 1 February 1878 -- 12 November 1955 ) was a Hungarian swimmer and architect .
Murry S. King ( 1870 - -1925 ) ( often spelled `` Murray '' ) was Florida 's first registered architect , a noted American architect with a successful practice in Orlando , Florida , in the 1910s and 1920s .
Charles Shaw - Lefevre , 1st Viscount Eversley GCB , PC ( 22 February 1794 -- 28 December 1888 ) , was a British Whig politician .
Emilian Bukov ( Russian : Емилиа́н Не́стерович Бу́ков ; 8 August ( O.S. 26 July ) 1909 Kiliya , Odessa Oblast , Ukraine -- 17 October 1984 ) was a Soviet Moldavian writer and poet , recognized with the State Prize of the Moldavian SSR and honorary title of People 's Writer of the Moldavian SSR ( 1982 ) .
James Warnecombe or Warmecombe ( by 1523 - 21 February 1581 ) , of Ivington , Herefordshire , was an English politician .
Major General Douangchay Phichit ( 5 April 1944 -- 17 May 2014 ) was a Laotian politician from Attapeu and a Politburo member of the Lao People 's Revolutionary Party ( from the 7th Congress of the Lao People 's Revolutionary Party until his death ) .
Ronald Eckersley ( born 4 September 1925 , Bingley , Yorkshire , England - 30 May 2009 ) is an English former first - class cricketer , who played one match for Yorkshire County Cricket Club against the Royal Air Force , at North Marine Road Ground , Scarborough in 1945 .
William Korey ( 16 June 1922 -- 26 August 2009 ) was a lobbyist on international issues for B’nai B’rith .
Egfrid of Lindisfarne ( also known as Heathured ) was Bishop of Lindisfarne from 821 until his death in 830 .
John deKoven Hill ( 1920 - 1996 ) was an American architect , honorary chairman of the Frank Lloyd Wright Foundation and editorial director of House Beautiful magazine .
Einar Woxen , MBE ( 5 November 1878 -- 12 November 1937 ) was a Norwegian barrister and journalist .
Father George Kandathil SJ ( 25 December 1920 -- 7 November 2011 ) is the pioneer of transactional analysis ( TA ) in India .
Gaston Redon ( 1853 - -1921 ) was a French architect , teacher , and graphic artist .
Sheikh Gad al - Haq Ali Gad al - Haq ( 5 April 1917 - 15 March 1996 ) was Grand Imam of Al - Azhar from 1982 to 1996 .
John Wilson - Patten , 1st Baron Winmarleigh PC ( 26 April 1802 -- 11 July 1892 ) was a British Conservative politician .
Nancy Keesing ( 7 September 1923 -- 19 January 1993 ) was a Jewish Australian writer and editor .
Thomas Nuthall ( died 7 March 1775 ) was an English politician and attorney who played an historic role in the ministries of William Pitt , Lord Bute , and Lord Rockingham .
W. Dorr Legg ( born William Dorr Lambert Legg 1904 - -July 26 , 1994 ) , was a landscape architect and one of the founders of the United States gay rights movement , then called the homophile movement .
John Meinhard VII , Count of Gorizia ( 1378 or 1380 -- 22 May 1430 ) was a member of the Meinhardiner dynasty .
Baldwin Hyde ( died 16 August 1472 ) was a Canon of Windsor from 1469 to 1472 and Clerk of the Parliaments 1470 - 1741
Grazioso Rusca ( 1757 -- 18 June 1829 ) was a Swiss sculptor who was also active in northern Italy .
Aksel Frederik Andersen ( 10 February 1891 Fodby , Denmark -- 1972 Gentofte , Denmark ) was a Danish mathematician who worked on infinite series and in particular on Cesàro summation .
John Gillespie Magee , Jr. ( 9 June 1922 -- 11 December 1941 ) was an American aviator and poet , made famous for his poem High Flight .
Elizabeth Needham ( died 3 May 1731 ) , also known as Mother Needham , was an English procuress and brothel - keeper of 18th - century London , who has been identified as the bawd greeting Moll Hackabout in the first plate of William Hogarth 's series of satirical etchings , A Harlot 's Progress .
Gonçalo Álvares ( ? ? -- 1524 ) was a Portuguese explorer who actively participated in the age of discovery starting from the second voyage of Diogo Cão .
Luis Augusto Turcios Lima ( 23 November 1941 - 2 October 1966 ) was a Guatemalan army officer and leader of the Rebel Armed Forces ( Fuerzas Armadas Rebeldes , or FAR ) .
John Guildesborough or Gildesburgh ( c. 1331 -- 1389 ) was Knight of the Shire for Essex and Speaker of the House of Commons of England in 1380 .
Štefan Uher ( 4 June 1930 -- 29 March 1993 ) was a Slovak film director , one of the founders of the `` Czechoslovak New Wave '' .
Guan Bo ( 關播 ) ( 719 -- February 4 , 797 ) , courtesy name Wuyuan ( 務元 ) , was an official of the Chinese dynasty Tang Dynasty , serving as a chancellor during the reign of Emperor Dezong .
William Hone ( 3 June 1780 -- 8 November 1842 ) was an English writer , satirist and bookseller .
Robert Besley ( 1794 - -1876 ) was an English typographer , creator of Clarendon ( typeface ) in 1845 and the Lord Mayor of London in 1869 .
John Goller ( died 1874 ) was a pioneer settler in Los Angeles , California , as a result of the great gold rush of 1849 , escaping with his life during a perilous crossing of the desert and claiming he had found prodigious gold deposits there .
Rolv Høiland ( 26 September 1926 -- 2001 ) was a Norwegian magazine editor .
Totti Truman Taylor , born Dorothy Leah Pedley ( 7 September 1915 -- 5 March 1981 ) , was a British actress .
Panagiotis Paraskevopoulos ( Greek : Παναγιώτης Παρασκευόπουλος , 1875 --8 July 1956 ) was a Greek athlete .
Vic Bodsworth ( 10 July 1931 -- 3 December 1967 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Footscray in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Leslie Waddington ( 9 February 1934 -- 30 November 2015 ) was a British art dealer who served as the chairman of Waddington Custot Galleries , 11 Cork Street , London .
Karel Rychlík ( Czech pronunciation : ( ˈkarɛl ˈrɪxliːk ) ; 1885 - -1968 ) was a Czech mathematician who contributed significantly to the fields of algebra , number theory , mathematical analysis , and the history of mathematics .
Pedro Medina Avendaño ( 14 September 1915 -- 31 August 2012 ) was a Colombian lawyer and poet , author of the Anthem of Bogotá and the Anthem of Boyacá , he was also known as the `` Poet of the Anthems '' .
Phannias ben Samuel ( in Hebrew : פנחס בן שמואל Pinhas ben Shmuel ) ( c. 70 CE ) was the last Jewish High Priest .
Humphrey Walrond ( c. 1600 -- c. 1670 ) , was Deputy - Governor of Barbados .
Ram Vilas Sharma ( 10 October 1912 -- 30 May 2000 ) was an eminent progressive literary critic , linguist , poet and thinker .
Di Qing ( 1008 - -1057 ) , formerly romanized as Ti Ch'ing , was a military general of the Northern Song dynasty .
Air Chief Marshal Nikolaos Stapas ( Greek : Νικόλαος Στάπας , 1937 -- 14 June 2011 ) was a Greek Air Force officer and Chief of the Hellenic Air Force General Staff .
Alan Ruddock ( 10 January 1944 -- 2 April 2012 ) was an Irish Martial Arts pioneer , teacher and writer .
John Stuart , Lord Mount Stuart ( 25 September 1767 -- 22 January 1794 ) , was an England - born Scottish Tory politician .
John William Warde was a twenty - six - year - old native of Southampton , New York who committed suicide on July 26 , 1938 .
Frederic Thesiger , 1st Baron Chelmsford PC KC FRS ( 25 April 1794 -- 5 October 1878 ) was a British jurist and Conservative politician .
Carola Goya ( 1906 - -1994 ) was an American dancer , choreographer , and teacher who specialized in the study and performance of Spanish dance .
Ekaterina Sankovskaya ( 1816 , Moscow - 28 August 1878 , Moscow ) was a Russian dancer who graduated from the Moscow Bolshoi Ballet School in 1836 .
Nicolaas Jan van Strien ( 1 April 1946 -- 7 February 2008 ) , or just Nico van Strien , was a zoologist and conservationist of Dutch ancestry .
William Young Fullerton ( 8 March 1857 -- 17 August 1932 ) was a Baptist preacher , administrator and writer .
Athanasios Kanakaris - Roufos ( Greek : Αθανάσιος Κανακάρης-Ρούφος , 1830 - -1902 ) was a Greek politician from Achaea .
Yngvar Sonnichsen ( March 9 , 1873 -- July 1938 ) was a Norwegian born , American artist and painter known especially for his portraits , landscapes and murals .
Edward Liddall Armitage or E. Liddall Armitage ( 1887 - 1967 ) was an English stained glass artist .
William Primrose CBE ( 23 August 1904 -- 1 May 1982 ) was a Scottish violist and teacher .
Max Benedict ( 20 February 1920 -- 20 April , 1986 ) was an Austrian born , British film editor .
Harvey John Tompkins , M.D. ( 1906 - -1983 ) was an American physician , a psychiatrist , whose professional life was in public service .
Hermione Cobbold , Baroness Cobbold ( born Margaret Hermione Millicent Bulwer - Lytton ; 31 August 1905 -- 27 October 2004 ) , known as Lady Hermione Bulwer - Lytton until 1930 , was the British matriarch of Knebworth House and wife of Cameron Fromanteel Cobbold , 1st Baron Cobbold .
Adam Adami , O.S.B. ( 1603 or 1610 -- 19 February 1663 ) was a German monk , diplomat and priest .
Jacques Maroger ( French pronunciation : ​(maʁoʒe ) ; 1884 - -1962 ) was a painter and the technical director of the Louvre Museum 's laboratory in Paris .
Philipp Otto Runge ( German : ( ˈʀʊŋə ) ; 23 July 1777 -- 2 December 1810 ) was a Romantic German painter and draughtsman .
James Grimble Groves ( 24 October 1854 -- 23 June 1914 ) was a British brewer and Conservative politician .
Iconologia di Cesare Ripa Perugino ... : divisa in tre libri , by Cesare Ripa , Cristoforo Tomassini publisher , Venice , 1645 .
Sun Yuanheng ( 孫元亨 ) ( died October 26 , 696 ) was an official of Wu Zetian 's Zhou Dynasty , serving briefly as chancellor .
James Durbin FBA ( 30 June 1923 -- 23 June 2012 ) was a British statistician and econometrician , known particularly for his work on time series analysis and serial correlation .
Terence Harris MBE ( 6 July 1939 -- 18 March 2011 ) , known as Jet Harris , was an English musician .
Sir Thomas Dale ( died 19 August 1619 ) was an English naval commander and deputy - governor of the Virginia Colony in 1611 and from 1614 to 1616 .
Joe Slovo ( 23 May 1926 -- 6 January 1995 , full name Yossel Mashel Slovo ) was a South African politician , an opponent of the apartheid system .
Ernest J. Burrus ( 1907 - 1991 ) was a Jesuit and a leading historian of northwestern New Spain , particularly the Baja California peninsula and Sonora .
Richard Henry Meade ( 1814 - 23 December 1899 in Bradford , England ) was an English surgeon , and Justice of the peace .
Franz Xaver Oberleitner ( 12 January 1789 -- 10 June 1832 ) was an Austrian theologian and orientalist .
The Reverend John Wakeford ( died 13 February 1930 ) was a Church of England clergyman who was convicted of adultery and deprived of his post as Archdeacon of Stow in a celebrated court case in 1921 .
Willem Tomberg ( 1670 , Gouda -- 1712 , Gouda ) , was an 18th - century writer and stained glass painter .
Mehmet Arif Şenerim ( 1877 - -1951 ) was a Turkish military leader active during the Balkan Wars , the First World War , and the Turkish War of Independence .
Gnanendramohan Tagore ( also Gyanendramohan Tagore ) ( 24 January 1826 -- 5 January 1890 ) was the first Asian to be called to the bar in England , in 1862 .
Sylvester Phelps Hodgdon ( 1830 - -1906 ) was a prolific American painter .
Simon Gipps - Kent ( born Simon Trevor Kent ; 25 October 1958 -- 16 September 1987 ) was a prolific 20th century English theatre and film actor in the 1970s-80s , noted for his teen portrayals of British royalty and nobility .
Lyle Benjamin Borst ( 24 November 1912 -- 30 July 2002 ) , nuclear physicist , inventor , worked with Enrico Fermi in Chicago , involved with the Manhattan District Project , and worked with Ernest O. Wollan to conduct neutron scattering and neutron diffraction studies .
Leonard Gyllenhaal ( 3 December 1752 -- 13 May 1840 ) was a Swedish military officer and entomologist .
Li Cunjin ( 李存進 ) ( 857 - -922 ) , originally Sun Chongjin ( 孫重進 ) , was a military general in imperial China 's Tang Dynasty , and later the Jin territory in the ensuing Five Dynasties and Ten Kingdoms period after Tang 's collapse .
Gábor Ugron de Ábránfalva the Younger ( 8 January 1880 -- 27 October 1960 ) was a Hungarian politician , a member of one of the oldest noble families of Transylvania , who served as Interior Minister between 1917 and 1918 .
John Kitto ( 4 December 1804 -- 25 November 1854 ) was an English biblical scholar of Cornish descent .
Peder Als ( 16 May 1725 -- 8 July 1775 ) was a Danish historical and portrait painter
John Olaf Todahl ( 1884 - -1924 ) was an American illustrator and cartoonist .
Marshall Earle Reid ( August 31 , 1887 - December 5 , 1955 ) was a pioneer early aviator .
Joseph - Dominique - Emmanuel Le Moyne de Longueuil ( April 2 , 1738 -- January 19 , 1807 ) was a soldier , seigneur and politician in New France and Quebec .
Leonard Woodward ( died 5 June 1976 ) was a British chemist who was associated with the University of Oxford for more than 30 years , and who was a leading authority in the field of Raman spectroscopy .
John Fergus O'Hea ( b. c. 1838 ; d. 2 September 1922 ) was an Irish political cartoonist who sometimes published under the pseudonym Spex .
Antoni Szuniewicz ( 14 November 1911 in Leonowicze near Wilno - 12 March 1987 in Częstochowa ) was a Polish organist , composer , conductor , choirmaster and music teacher .
Umberto Melnati ( 17 June 1897 -- 30 March 1979 ) was an Italian film actor He appeared in over 35 films between 1932 and 1962 .
Brigadier Martin Melvin Cruickshank CIE FRSE FRCSE FACS FICS ( 1888 - 1964 ) was a Scottish surgeon , specialising in ophthalmic surgery .
William Hagan DuBarry ( 1894 - -1958 ) was the acting President of the University of Pennsylvania during parts of 1950 - 51 , 1952 , and 1953 .
Pedro de Peralta ( c. 1584 -- 1666 ) was Governor of New Mexico between 1610 and 1613 at a time when it was a province of New Spain .
Peter Malberg ( 21 September 1887 -- 23 June 1965 ) was a Danish actor best known for his role as Onkel Anders in the Far Til Fire movies .
Rabbi David Messas ( 15 July 1934 in Meknes , Morocco -- 20 November 2011 Paris ) was the son of Rabbi Chalom Messas , the former Chief Rabbi of Morocco who subsequently became the sefardic Chief Rabbi of Jerusalem .
Sir George Thorold , 1st Baronet ( c. 1666 -- 29 October 1722 ) of Harmston , Lincolnshire , was a leading London merchant .
Helena Kara ( originally Aini Helena Dahl , 16 August 1916 -- 26 February 2002 ) was a Finnish film actress .
Nikolaos Kantounis ( Greek : Νικόλαος Καντούνης ; 1767 , Zakynthos -- 1834 , Zakynthos ) was a Greek painter ; one of the most important representatives of the Heptanese School .
Frank Perkins Whitman ( 1853 - -1919 ) , was an American physicist
Clement Shahbaz Bhatti ( 9 September 1968 -- 2 March 2011 ) , popularly known as Shahbaz Bhatti , was a Pakistani politician and elected member of the National Assembly from 2008 .
Frederick Donald Blake RI , RSMA ( 1908 - -1997 ) was a Scottish artist .
Captain Sir Henry Chamberlain , 2nd Baronet ( 2 October 1796 -- 8 September 1843 ) was a British Army officer of the Royal Artillery and an artist whose series of drawings of Brazil were well known in his time .
Julia von Mengden ( Augusta Juliane ) ( 1719 - -1786 ) , was a Livonian noblewoman , lady in waiting , favourite and the intimate friend and confidante of the Russian regent Grand Duchess Anna Leopoldovna .
Tobias Hess ( 1558 - -1614 ) was a German lawyer based in Tübingen .
Justus Ferdinand Poggenburg III ( January 23 , 1895 - December 1966 ) was an American billiards champion .
John Cradock ( alias Craddock ) ( c. 1708 - 10 December 1778 ) was an English churchman , Church of Ireland Archbishop of Dublin from 1772 .
Yente Serdatzky ( Serdatsky ) ( 15 September 1877 -- 1 May 1962 ) was a Jewish - American Yiddish - language writer .
Alfred Rutter Clarke ( 17 November 1867 -- 10 December 1932 ) , generally referred to as `` Rutter Clarke '' or `` A. Rutter Clarke '' , was an Australian stockbroker and investor whose company Clarke and Co. , founded by his grandfather , William Clarke , operated in three states , and specialised in mining ventures .
Henry of Schweinfurt ( de Suinvorde ; c. 970 -- 18 September 1017 ) was the Margrave of the Nordgau from 994 until 1004 .
Samuel Tertius Galton ( 23 March 1783 -- 30 March 1844 ) was a businessman and scientist .
Asen Lekarski ( Bulgarian : Асен Лекарски ) ( 12 May 1901 -- 2 September 1952 ) was a Bulgarian fencer .
Ewart Bryon Butler ( 5 June 1934 -- 26 April 2001 ) was an English writer and broadcaster , best known as the BBC 's football correspondent from 1968 to 1991 .
John Alexander Lillington ( c. 1725 -- 1786 ) , also known as Alexander John Lillington , was a Patriot officer from North Carolina in the American Revolutionary War who notably fought in the Battle of Moore 's Creek Bridge in 1776 .
María del Socorro Bustamante ( 17 February 1955 -- 20 March 2015 ) was a Colombian politician who was a Senator from 1994 to 2002 .
Celestine Tate Harrington ( 1956 -- February 25 , 1998 ) was a quadriplegic street musician who was well known for playing the keyboard with her lips , teeth and tongue on the boardwalk .
Ilma Grace Stone ( 1913 -- 2001 ) , née Balfe , was an Australian botanist who specialised in bryology .
Conrad Detrez ( 1 April 1937 Roclenge - sur - Geer -- 12 February 1985 ) was a Belgian novelist .
John Goodwin Lyman ( 29 September 1886 -- 26 May 1967 ) was an American - born Canadian modernist painter active largely in Montreal .
Quang Nhuong Huynh ( August 22 , 1946 - -2001 ) was a Vietnamese - born American author .
William Mace ( died 1767 ) was an English Gresham Professor of Law , from 1744 , and Fellow of the Royal Society .
Gabriele Sforza died on 12 September 1457 in Milan and was buried in the church of Santa Maria Incoronata , Milan , which his brother had commissioned .
Zygmunt Kałużyński ( 11 December 1918 -- 30 September 2004 ) was a Polish lawyer , film critic , promoter of cinema , erudite , long - time contributor of Polityka magazine and a TV personality .
Iris Davies ( 1935 -- 20 July 2010 ) , pen name Iris Gower , was a novelist , noted for her many historical romances , most of which are set in the Welsh seaport of Swansea and the adjacent Gower Peninsula , from which she took her nom - de - plume .
Sir James Douglas , 7th of Drumlanrig , ( d. 1578 ) was a Scottish nobleman .
Dennis Hodgetts ( 28 November 1863 -- 26 March 1945 ) , commonly known as Denny Hodgetts , was a footballer in the early years of professional football in England .
Charles Henry Chomley ( 28 April 1868 -- 21 October 1942 ) was an Australian farmer , barrister , writer and journalist .
Frank Cyril Tiarks OBE ( also known as FC Tiarks ) ( Balham , 9 July 1874 -- Loxton , 7 April 1952 ) was an English banker .
Douglas Durkin ( 9 July 1884 - 4 June 1967 ) was a Canadian novelist , short story writer and screenwriter .
Amanieu VIII ( sometimes VII ) ( died 1326 ) was the Lord of Albret from 1298 until his death .
Edward the Martyr ( Old English : Eadweard ; c. 962 -- 18 March 978 ) was King of England from 975 until he was murdered in 978 .
Francisco Ruiz Lozano ( 1607 , Oruro , Alto Perú--1677 , Mexico City ) was a Peruvian soldier , astronomer , mathematician and educator .
Henry Coke ( 1591 - -1661 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons variously between 1624 and 1642 .
Hou Sizhi ( 侯思止 ) ( died 693 ) was a secret police official during the Chinese dynasty Tang Dynasty and Wu Zetian 's Zhou Dynasty .
Zelimkhan Murdalov was a 26-year - old student from Grozny , Chechnya , who left his home on January 2 , 2001 , saying he would return but never did .
Stefan Sadorski ( 1581 -- 2 July 1640 ) was a courtier , politician and a diplomat of the Polish - Lithuanian Commonwealth .
George Legge , 3rd Earl of Dartmouth KG , PC , FRS ( 3 October 1755 -- 10 November 1810 ) , styled Viscount Lewisham until 1801 , was a British politician .
Jānis Rieksts ( or Reeksts ; 21 May 1881 -- 24 November 1970 ) was a Latvian autodidact photographer .
Vassilis Steriadis ( Greek : Βασίλης Στεριάδης ; 1947 - -2003 ) was a Greek poet and critic .
Roman Zenzinger(16 July 1903 -- 5 November 1990 ) was an Austrian artist and commercial designer best known for his intense portraits and sketches of soldiers during world war II .
Ramchandra Bhikaji Gunjikar ( Devanagari : रामचंद्र भिकाजी गुंजीकर ) ( 1843 - 1901 ) was a Marathi writer from Maharashtra , India .
Frederick Oliver Robinson ( August 2 , 1903 - -June 26 , 1969 ) was an Ontario machinist and political figure .
Zacheus Chukwukaelo Obi , ( 1896 - 1993 ) Eze - onunekwulu - Igbo , ( spokesman for the Igbo ) was an Igbo leader who was born in Nnewi ; he was educated at the C.M.S. school , Nnewi .
Belgin Doruk ( 28 June 1936 , Ankara -- 26 March 1995 , Istanbul ) was a popular Turkish film actress .
Salomon de Bray ( 1597 -- 11 May 1664 ) was a Dutch Golden Age architect and painter .
Jesse Gray ( May 14 , 1923 -- January 2 , 1988 ) was an American civil rights leader and politician from New York .
Magdalena Andersdotter ( 1590 in Norway -- 1650 ) was a Norwegian shipowner .
Peter Hodge ( 18 June 1871 -- 18 August 1934 ) was a Scottish football manager who managed Raith Rovers , Stoke City , Manchester City and spent most of his career with Leicester City ( over two spells ) .
Paul Amman ( 31 August 1634 -- 4 February 1691 ) , German physician and botanist .
Giovanni Costanzi ( 1674 - -1754 ) was an Italian gem engraver of the late - Baroque period .
Lieutenant - General Sir David Willison KCB , OBE , MC ( 25 December 1919 -- 24 April 2009 ) was a British soldier who served with the Royal Engineers between 1939 and 1963 , after which he served in a series of military intelligence roles until his retirement from the army in 1975 .
Georges Grisez ( 31 March 1884 -- March 1946 ) was a French - born American clarinetist .
William Kearsley ( 2 September 1863 -- 19 June 1921 ) was an Australian politician and member of the New South Wales Legislative Assembly from 1910 until 1921 .
Josefina Méndez ( nickname Yuyi ; 8 March 1941 -- 26 January 2007 ) was a Cuban ballet dancer and ballet mistress .
